edu.umn.se.trap.data
Class ReimbursementApp

java.lang.Object
  edu.umn.se.trap.data.ReimbursementApp

public class ReimbursementApp
extends java.lang.Object

A large data object that holds the hierarchy of objects and attributes that represent an the equivalent of an input form's data. The purpose for this data object is to make it simpler for rules and later processing to access form data without being dependent on the format of the input data.

Author:
andrewh

addToReimbursementTotal

public void addToReimbursementTotal(java.lang.Double amount)
Add to the reimbursement total amount. If you are adding an amount pertaining to a MealExpense, LodgingExpense, or IncidentalExpense you must use the addtoPerDiemTotal(Double, Integer) method. Essentially, if you are dealing with any expense type that is held by a TripDay you should use the other method.

Parameters:
amount - - The amount to add to the total
See Also:
getReimbursementTotal()

addtoPerDiemTotal

public void addtoPerDiemTotal(java.lang.Double amount,
                              java.lang.Integer dayNum)
This will add an expense amount to both the reimbursementTotal as well as the TripDay corresponding to the day number provided.

Parameters:
amount - - The amount to add
dayNum - - The day to add it under. (will also be added to grand total)
